This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House, regarding the issuance of an Executive Order to address the Russian occupation of the Crimea region of Ukraine. The order prohibits new investment by US persons in Crimea, as well as the importation and exportation of goods, services, or technology to and from Crimea. It also blocks the property and interests in property of certain individuals and entities operating in Crimea. Additionally, the order suspends entry into the US of aliens meeting certain criteria. The President has delegated the authority to the Secretary of the Treasury to take necessary actions to carry out the order.